             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am servant to Mr. Thwaite, a <rs id="t17790707-37-viclabel183" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17790707-37-victim413 t17790707-37-viclabel183"></join> at the <placeName id="t17790707-37-crimeloc184">Seven Dials</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17790707-37-crimeloc184" type="placeName" value="Seven Dials"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17790707-37-crimeloc184" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17790707-37-off181 t17790707-37-crimeloc184"></join>. On the 28th of June the prisoner and another woman came into our shop and asked to be shown some cloth; I showed her several pieces, which she did not like; I had a suspicion of her; she at last asked the price of a piece; I told her it was one shilling a yard; she bid me cut off three-fourths of a yard. As I was cutting it off, I looked in her face and saw her change colour very much; and as she was going out I saw she had something under her apron; I stopped her, and found this piece of cloth (producing it) under her apron; it is my master's property; it has his mark upon it.</p>
               <p>Mr. Thwaite. It is my property; I saw my man take it from her.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I had not the linen; I know nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17790707-37-verdict185" type="verdictDescription">
